just_use spectator.py

# label: EARLY (agent-side CRUD-HTML reader)
# role: agent tool — read-only view of Gopher games via HTTP scrape

Acts like a human browsing Gopher: HTTP Basic auth to the
CRUD pages on port 9000, parses HTML with BeautifulSoup. No
DB reach-around — the whole point is to validate the CRUD
pages are readable (and by extension, agent-usable) per
`project_crud_html_simplicity.md`.

## Status (TENTATIVE)

Labeled EARLY. The tool has been exercised in LynRummy
contexts pre-refactor; post-refactor robustness unverified.
The LynRummy UI is now Elm (not CRUD HTML), so this is more
useful for non-LynRummy Gopher features (issues, wiki,
etc.) than for the current LynRummy surface.

## Auth

Env vars `GOPHER_EMAIL` + `GOPHER_API_KEY`, or `--email` /
`--api-key` flags. Base URL `GOPHER_BASE` (default
`http://localhost:9000`).

## Commands

- `list` — show all visible games.
- `show <id>` — show game detail + event log.

## Relation to the HTTP-when-bridge rule

`feedback_http_when_bridge.md` — this tool is HTTP-based
because Gopher CRUD is the canonical agent interface for
admin-style scrape. Good fit for the rule. One-way
analytical tools (like `telemetry.py`) bypass HTTP.

## Pointers

- Memory: `project_crud_html_simplicity.md` (forcing
  function for simple HTML).
